edu.ucla.sspace.util
Class HashMultiMap<K,V>

java.lang.Object
  edu.ucla.sspace.util.HashMultiMap<K,V>
All Implemented Interfaces:
MultiMap<K,V>, Serializable
public class HashMultiMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements MultiMap<K,V>, Serializable

A hash table based implementation of the MultiMap interface. This implementation permits both null keys and values.

This implementation provides constant time operations for the basic operations put and get, assuming a uniform distribution of hash keys.

See Also:
HashMap, Serialized Form

range

public int range()
Returns the number of values maped to keys. Note that in the bijective case, this will equal the value returned by MultiMap.size(). However, in the case where a key is mapped to more than one value, this method will always return a value strictly larger than size().

remove

public boolean remove(Object key,
                      Object value)
Removes the specified mapping for a key if it is present. If the key is mapped to other values, it is retained, otherwise the key is removed from the map. This method provides a way to remove a specific mapping for a key without removing all other existing mappings.
